{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "This project used the Math and Portuguese data set from the UCI machine learning repository to create classifiers for 2-class and 5-class predictions.",
    "The proposed system outperformed other models and achieved an accuracy of 96.6%.",
    "To predict course grades, Zhang et al (2023) suggested a model using a Multisource sparse attention Convolutional Neural Network (MsaCNN).",
    "MsaCNN uses several input-heads to combine multi-source features, multi-scale convolution kernels on student grade records to identify structural features, and a global attention layer to identify the relationships between courses.",
    "A softmax classifier was then fed with all the obtained features to create a DL model."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "To predict course grades, Zhang et al (2023) suggested a model using a Multisource sparse attention Convolutional Neural Network (MsaCNN)."
  ]
}